      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُهُ عَنْ مُحْرِمٍ أَصَابَ أَرْنَباً أَوْ ثَعْلَباً قَالَ «فِي اَلْأَرْنَبِ دَمُ شَاةٍ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2727 - Al-Bazanti narrated from Abu al-Hasan (as), who said: I asked him about a person in the state of ihram who hunted a rabbit or a fox.\nImam (as) said: \"For the rabbit, the expiation is the sacrifice of a sheep.\""
        ]
      }
